    <strong>1. Dignity of the Courts</strong>
    <p>
      It is important that any analysis maintains the dignity of the courts and tribunals and does not undermine their functioning as working bodies. This is consistent with access to justice.
    </p>
    <p>Licence holders must not undermine the courts and tribunals’ ability to function as working bodies.</p>
    <p>
      You should consider anything that may undermine the ability for the justice system to operate impartially and with integrity and treat all members of the public equally and fairly,
